					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 12 sheep left in charge of the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Śiṟu-Paḻuvūr by Rāmaṉ Kōviyār wife of Paḻuvēṭṭaraiyar Vikramāditya for burning a lamp in the temple of Tiruvālanduṟai-Mahādēva, with a <hi rend="italic">piḍi</hi> of ghee supplied every day. This is probably an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
